# Feature-Level Workflow

Before implementing any feature, check whether a feature folder exists.

A valid feature folder should contain:
- `PRD.md`
- `TECH_SPEC.md`
- `TASKS.md`
- `DECISIONS.md`

If the feature folder does not exist:
1. Create it under `docs/features/[next-number]-[kebab-case-feature-name]/`
2. Copy from `docs/templates/`
3. Fill in the docs based on global architecture
4. Do not write application code yet

When implementing:
- Follow the feature PRD.
- Follow the feature tech spec.
- Complete tasks one at a time.
- Do not build items listed as out of scope.
- Do not change global architecture unless necessary.

After implementing:
- Update feature `TASKS.md`.
- Update feature status if complete.
- Add decisions to feature `DECISIONS.md`.
- If global architecture changes, update `docs/architecture/DECISIONS.md`.
